'''''Star Wars Insider'' 48''' is the forty-eighth issue of ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine. It was released to newsstands on [[April 4]], [[2000]].

==Contents==
===Departments===
*"[[Rebel Rumblings]]"
*"[[Prequel Update]] with [[Rick McCallum]]" {{C|by [[Dan Madsen]]}}
*"[[Star News]]"
*"[[In the Star Wars Universe|In the ''Star Wars'' Universe]]: [[Jerome Blake]]"
*"[[The Horse's Mouth]]" &mdash; Tale Spinning {{C|by [[Peeja Mobet]]}}
*"[[Bookshelf|''Star Wars'' Bookshelf]]" &mdash; Dark Tide Rising: Mike Stackpole Unleashes the ''Onslaught'' {{C|by Jason Fry}}
*"[[Scouting the Galaxy]]" &mdash; Bring Me the Head of Darth Maul {{C|by [[Stephen J. Sansweet]]}}
*"[[The Jawa Trader]]"
*"[[The Last Page]]"

===Features===
*"[[George Lucas in Love]]" {{C|by [[Brian F. McCoughey]]}}
*:<small>Joining the ranks of ''Hardware Wars'' and ''Troops'', the new short film spoof ''George Lucas in Love'' has become an instant fan classic—and gotten its creators on the Hollywood fast track. Brian F. McCoughey talks to the filmmakers about how they did it.</small>
*"[[Episode I Easter Eggs|Episode I Easter Egg Hunt!]]" {{C|by [[Mark Cotta Vaz]]}}
*:<small>It's time to put the rumors to rest, as the ''Insider'' goes on a hunt for the secret images, jokes, and cameos (known as Easter Eggs) hidden throughout ''The Phantom Menace''. [[Mark Cotta Vaz]] goes behind the scenes with ILM to debunk the myths and uncover Easter Eggs not yet found. From E.T.s to ''Blade Runner'' to lawn mowers, it's all here!</small>
*"[[Voices of Episode I]]" {{C|by [[Jason Fry]]}}
*:<small>Get face-to-face with the talented actors who lent their voices to some of the greatest characters in the latest ''Star Wars'' episode. [[Jason Fry]] lends an ear to the performers behind [[Watto/Legends|Watto]], [[Sebulba/Legends|Sebulba]], [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Roos Tarpals/Legends|Tarpals]], [[Darth Maul/Legends|Darth Maul]], [[TC-14/Legends|TC-14]], and both [[Fodesinbeed Annodue/Legends|Fode]] ''and'' Beed. Hear ye, hear ye!</small>
*"[[Decipher This!]]"
*:<small>They came, they saw, they conquered. The brave competitors for the ''Star Wars'' [[Star Wars Customizable Card Game|CCG]] World Championship met at the 1999 Decipher Con in Virginia Beach, and the ''Insider''{{'s}} [[Rich Handley]] was there to watch the winners.</small>
*"[[Ray Park: Life After Darth]]" {{C|by [[Scott Chernoff]]}}
*:<small>Now that Darth Maul's been split in two, just what the heck is actor Ray Park going to do? Well, star in ''X-Men'', for one thing—and slice-and-dice in ''Sleepy Hollow'' for another. [[Scott Chernoff]] catches up with Park one year after his first ''Insider'' interview to reflect on his summer of ''Star Wars'' and look ahead to his burgeoning feature film career.</small>
*"[[Star Wars Road Trip|''Star Wars'' Road Trip]]" {{C|by [[David West Reynolds (real person)|David West Reynolds]]}}
*:<small>Fasten your seat belts—it's the ''Insider''{{'s}} comprehensive and adventure-filled exploration of all the places ''you'' can go where ''Star Wars'' was filmed in the United States, including the [[Tatooine/Legends|Tatooine]] dunes of [[Death Valley]] and [[Yuma]], the [[Endor/Legends|Endorian]] forests of Northern California—and a lot more. [[David West Reynolds]] and Scott Chernoff take a look back at the original location shooting and find the Death Valley spots again. Plus, your handy road map and written directions so you can make the ''Star Wars'' Road Trip yourself. All that and a cool contest, too!</small>
*"[[All Decked Out!]]" {{C|by [[Rich Handley]]}}

